headline: Did the Howard Street Tunnel Upgrade Just Shift CSX’s (CSX) Network Efficiency and Growth Narrative?
summary: CSX Corporation recently completed the early reopening of the modernized Howard Street Tunnel in Baltimore, a US$450 million infrastructure project aimed at boosting freight rail capacity and efficiency through collaboration with federal and state agencies. This development removes a significant bottleneck for double-stacked trains along the vital I-95 corridor, underscoring CSX's role in facilitating major logistics improvements on the East Coast.
